A quantification of the detectable chemical elements was performed by peak deconvolution of all detailed spectra. In order to get additional information about the surface layers, XPS spectra were measured under three detection angles of 0°, 35° and 50° relative to the surface normal. As expected, we find increasing signals of surface layers with increasing detection angles. The attenuation of the photoelectron signal (I/I0) by inelastic scattering in a layer of the thickness (d) can be calculated by using the equation [41]:1II0=edλ·cosθ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
